SENATE RESOLUTION 67
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to commemorate the 250th anniversary of the
U.S. Army.
WHEREAS, the contributions and sacrifices of the men and women who have served in
the United States Army since its inception in 1775 have been vital in maintaining our freedoms
and way of life; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. Army will celebrate its 250th birthday on June 14, 2025,
commemorating its establishment on that date in 1775, more than one year before the signing
of the Declaration of Independence; and
WHEREAS, the Army was formed when the Second Continental Congress passed a
resolution that created a national Army of "six companies of expert riflemen" to join forces near
Boston; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. Army had a significant role in the growth and development of the
United States, winning the new republic's independence in an arduous eight-year struggle
against Great Britain; the Army remains committed to the security of our nation still today; and
WHEREAS, in honor of 250 years of devotion and history, there will be a wide-reaching,
inclusive celebration, with the anniversary theme "This We'll Defend," highlighting the Army's
ongoing commitment to protecting the nation; and
WHEREAS, the Army Historical Foundation is involved in the celebration, and the Army
Center of Military History is launching an eighteen-month awareness campaign about the
milestones of the U.S. Army in American history; and
WHEREAS, to further mark the 250th anniversary of the Army, the National Museum of
the U.S. Army will open a new exhibit focusing on the Revolutionary War in June 2025; there
